### 2. Stay True to Source Material - No Hallucinations

**CRITICAL: Only include content that exists in the source courses you're adapting from.**

**DON'T:**
- Add concepts not covered in source courses
- Invent new technical terms or sections
- Add "advanced" topics that weren't in the original material
- Create content from general knowledge

**DO:**
- Read the entire source lesson before adapting
- Only include concepts present in source material
- Adapt examples to workshop context, but keep concepts the same
- If you think additional content is needed, note it for review rather than adding it

**Example of Hallucination to AVOID:**
- Source course doesn't mention "fanout" ‚Üí Don't add a "Understanding Fanout" section
- Source course doesn't cover "denormalization strategies" ‚Üí Don't add that concept
- Source course has 3 relationship types ‚Üí Don't add 6 relationship types

