### 6. Mermaid Diagrams - Use Circles for Graph Nodes

**REQUIRED: Graph nodes must be circles, not boxes.**

**DON'T use boxes:**
```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Customer] -->|PLACED| B[Order]
    B -->|ORDERS| C[Product]
```

**DO use circles:**
```mermaid
graph LR
    A((Customer)) -->|PLACED| B((Order))
    B -->|ORDERS| C((Product))
```

**Alternative circle syntax:**
```mermaid
graph LR
    Customer((Customer)) -->|PLACED| Order((Order))
    Order -->|ORDERS| Product((Product))
```

**Rules:**
- Use `((NodeName))` for circle nodes
- Keep relationship labels clear and readable
- Use colors appropriately (current colors are fine)
- Ensure diagrams are simple and focused
- Limit to 3-6 nodes per diagram for clarity

